        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDuplicate for https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/cps/+/118132\n\nPlease also see that I responded to comments made in 118132.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8d1986a67ef921cf9da56ccac6b0e00c4f8c0068",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6679,
          "name": "Claudio David Gasparini",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gasparini24@gmail.com",
          "username": "cdgasparini"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-23 06:53:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Duplicate for https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/cps/+/118132\n> \n> Please also see that I responded to comments made in 118132.\n\nis not a duplicate, this commit fixes the root issue. Which is the capability to generate an image with wrong content.\nMeanwhile your commit is about service name and build process(skip image generation), plus there still some issues presents. e.g. if you execute \"mvn clean install -Djib.skip=false\" using your commit, it will try to generate an image and will fail because missconfiguration.\nWhen indeed, it should not even execute the plugin at all if not profile is selected.\n\nAnd that is what this commit is addressing, your changes proposal can still go on top of this one, since they address different things.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e40e9bb38184a2d47523977009b0afd7ecf40e6b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7362,
          "name": "Ruslan Kashapov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ruslan.kashapov@pantheon.tech",
          "username": "rkashapov"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-23 13:18:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "39cb15cbbb794b04fda1b0dbda8cce13f0dc2fc4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5658,
          "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
          "username": "brusak"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-23 15:52:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWe just need to  keep in mind that always generating the docker image also impacts `cps-maven-stage-master` job. By default, this job is also going to generate the docker image even if it is not is responsibility. `maven-docker-stage-master` job is responsible for that.\n\nThen, `cps-maven-stage-master` will need to be changed if we want to remove docker image from it. And the same would apply to any process that does not need docker or is docker independent.\n\nI'm not saying that we should not go that way if this is a CSIT requirement, this is just to highlight the impact.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "c9f29851afae8dd09763081665a671e3676ab0da",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6679,
          "name": "Claudio David Gasparini",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gasparini24@gmail.com",
          "username": "cdgasparini"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-23 15:59:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> We just need to  keep in mind that always generating the docker image also impacts `cps-maven-stage-master` job. By default, this job is also going to generate the docker image even if it is not is responsibility. `maven-docker-stage-master` job is responsible for that.\n> \n> Then, `cps-maven-stage-master` will need to be changed if we want to remove docker image from it. And the same would apply to any process that does not need docker or is docker independent.\n> \n> I'm not saying that we should not go that way if this is a CSIT requirement, this is just to highlight the impact.\n\nright (but it might use only local repo, not sure), and that is why I would like to have Lasse involved on the CSIT meeting to resolve all type of doubts from the team",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
